Docs.summary: Represents timesheet settings information as a row in the object.

remarks.para: Many of the TimeSheetSettingsRow properties represent settings on the Timesheet Settings and Defaults page (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/TSSettings.aspx) in Project Web App.
For a code sample that reads a TimeSheetSettingsDataSet and saves it to an XML file, see .

MemberSignature.Value: public: property int WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD { int get(); void set(int value); };
member this.WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD : int with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the default timesheet tracking method for reporting hours worked on tasks.

remarks.para: Return Values: Value=1: hours of work done per day or per week; Value=2: percent of work complete; Value=3: actual work done and work remaining.
The WADMIN_DEFAULT_TRACKING_METHOD property can be set on the Task Settings and Display page (http://ServerName/ProjectServerName/_layouts/pwa/Admin/TSSettings.aspx) in Project Web App.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool WADMIN_TS_FIXED_APPROVAL_ROUTING { bool get(); void set(bool value); };
member this.WADMIN_TS_FIXED_APPROVAL_ROUTING : bool with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies whether timesheet approval routing is fixed.

remarks.para: True if timesheet approval routing is fixed.

If WADMIN_TS_FIXED_APPROVAL_ROUTING is True, timesheets can only be submitted to the timesheet manager of the resource. If False, the resource is given a choice of who to submit the timesheet to for approval.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Decimal WADMIN_TS_HOURS_PER_DAY { System::Decimal get(); void set(System::Decimal value); };
member this.WADMIN_TS_HOURS_PER_DAY : decimal with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the number of hours in a standard timesheet day, in units of 1/1000th minute.

remarks.para: For an eight hour day, the value of WADMIN_TS_HOURS_PER_DAY would be 8 * 60000 = 480,000.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Decimal WADMIN_TS_HOURS_PER_WEEK { System::Decimal get(); void set(System::Decimal value); };
member this.WADMIN_TS_HOURS_PER_WEEK : decimal with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the number of hours in a standard timesheet work week, in units of 1/1000th minute.

remarks.para: For a 40 hour week, the value is 40 * 60000 = 2,400,000.

remarks.para: True if timesheet auditing is enabled.
When auditing is enabled, timesheet creation and changes to approval and adjustments are recorded.

When future reporting is disabled, timesheet users cannot enter time beyond the current day.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Decimal WADMIN_TS_MAX_HR_PER_DAY { System::Decimal get(); void set(System::Decimal value); };
member this.WADMIN_TS_MAX_HR_PER_DAY : decimal with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the maximum number of hours that can be recorded on a timesheet for one day of work.

remarks.para: The value is the number of hours * 60000. For example, a maximum of 8 hours per day is stored as 480000.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Decimal WADMIN_TS_MAX_HR_PER_TS { System::Decimal get(); void set(System::Decimal value); };
member this.WADMIN_TS_MAX_HR_PER_TS : decimal with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the maximum number of hours that can be recorded for a timesheet.

remarks.para: The value is the number of hours * 60000. For example, a maximum of 40 hours per timesheet is stored as 2400000.
To specify that there is no maximum limit, use a value of 999 hours (59940000).

MemberSignature.Value: public: property System::Decimal WADMIN_TS_MIN_HR_PER_TS { System::Decimal get(); void set(System::Decimal value); };
member this.WADMIN_TS_MIN_HR_PER_TS : decimal with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies the minimum number of hours that must be recorded for a timesheet.

remarks.para: The value is the number of hours * 60000. For example, a minimum of 30 minutes per timesheet is stored as 30000.
To specify that there is no minimum number of hours, use a value of 0.

member this.WADMIN_TS_PROJECT_MANAGER_APPROVAL : bool with get, set

Docs.summary: Specifies whether project manager approval is required on line items before a timesheet is sent for timesheet manager approval.

MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool WADMIN_TS_PROJECT_MANAGER_COORDINATION { bool get(); void set(bool value); };

Docs.summary: Specifies whether project managers can view line item approvals when a timesheet is submitted for approval.

remarks.para: True if project managers can view line item approvals.
When is true, WADMIN_TS_PROJECT_MANAGER_COORDINATION is always true.

Note: On a Project Web App site that is created from an upgrade of a site from Microsoft Office Project Server 2007, if you query for in the returned TimeSheetSettingsDataSet, you get a System.InvalidCastException. The field value is DBNull, so the application cannot cast to a Boolean value.
For a code sample that checks the value of WADMIN_TS_PROJECT_MANAGER_COORDINATION, see .
